    },
    {
      "id": "c8IHPIqDFDivUwHGaGDLA",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 295.1999816894531,
      "y": 204.70001220703125,
      "width": 939.7192993164062,
      "height": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1A",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1334094480,
      "version": 413,
      "versionNonce": 1694012528,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1768936149409,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Leetcode is a platform that helps software engineers / students prepare  for coding interviews.\nIt offers a vast collection of coding problems, ranging from easy to hard, and provides\na platform for users to answer questions and get feedback on their solutions.\nThey also run periodic coding competitions.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Leetcode is a platform that helps software engineers / students prepare  for coding interviews.\nIt offers a vast collection of coding problems, ranging from easy to hard, and provides\na platform for users to answer questions and get feedback on their solutions.\nThey also run periodic coding competitions.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "FymjXKp33nQtweLQ36g80",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 301.0223100450304,
      "y": 378.9888865152995,
      "width": 808.9993896484375,
      "height": 1425,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1C",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1195094160,
      "version": 1613,
      "versionNonce": 505952912,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1769333317778,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Functional Requirements\n\n- view a list of problems\n- view a given problem and code a solution for the same\n- submit the solution and get feedback\n- support competitions/contests with live leaderboard\n\n\nNon-functional Requirements\n\n- availability >> consistency\n- security and isolation when running users code\n- scale to support competitions with 100k users\n- fresh / near realtime leaderboard\n\n\nScale\n\n- 100k DAU (5M total accounts)\n- 3k problems\n- 100k peak users for competitions\n\n\nCore Entities\n\n- User\n- Problem\n- Submission\n- Competition\n- Leaderboard\n\n\nAPI\n\n// view a list of problems\nGET /problems?category={}&difficulty={}&page={}&size={} -> Partial<Problems[]>\n\n// view a specific problem\nGET /problems/:problemId\n\n// submit a solution\nPOST /problems/:problemId -> 200\n{\n    code,\n    language,\n    competitionId?\n}\n(If the code is very large, then it could be first submitted to AWS S3 and\n we get a S3 URL to that and send that link instead).\n\n// poll server for submit result every 3s\nGET /problems/:problemId/submissions/:submissionId -> Submission\n\n// get leaderboard\nGET /leaderboard/:competitionId?page={}&size={} -> Leaderboard\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Functional Requirements\n\n- view a list of problems\n- view a given problem and code a solution for the same\n- submit the solution and get feedback\n- support competitions/contests with live leaderboard\n\n\nNon-functional Requirements\n\n- availability >> consistency\n- security and isolation when running users code\n- scale to support competitions with 100k users\n- fresh / near realtime leaderboard\n\n\nScale\n\n- 100k DAU (5M total accounts)\n- 3k problems\n- 100k peak users for competitions\n\n\nCore Entities\n\n- User\n- Problem\n- Submission\n- Competition\n- Leaderboard\n\n\nAPI\n\n// view a list of problems\nGET /problems?category={}&difficulty={}&page={}&size={} -> Partial<Problems[]>\n\n// view a specific problem\nGET /problems/:problemId\n\n// submit a solution\nPOST /problems/:problemId -> 200\n{\n    code,\n    language,\n    competitionId?\n}\n(If the code is very large, then it could be first submitted to AWS S3 and\n we get a S3 URL to that and send that link instead).\n\n// poll server for submit result every 3s\nGET /problems/:problemId/submissions/:submissionId -> Submission\n\n// get leaderboard\nGET /leaderboard/:competitionId?page={}&size={} -> Leaderboard\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
