      "text": "VMs have a lot of overhead, they run entire os by themselves,\nslow to startup and requires lot of resources.\n\nContainers on the other hand, share the host's os and only\npackages the applications code and dependencies, lightweight,\nallows us to run more instances on the same hardware.\n\nServerless functions : AWS Lambda - small, stateless, event-driven\nfunctions. They run in response to triggers like- https request.\nManaged by cloud provider, autoscaled on demand.\nCold start problem. But, AWS team has some strategies to warmup\nby keeping some ready server for each runtime, which basically is\nthe same as our docker containers.\n\n",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "VMs have a lot of overhead, they run entire os by themselves,\nslow to startup and requires lot of resources.\n\nContainers on the other hand, share the host's os and only\npackages the applications code and dependencies, lightweight,\nallows us to run more instances on the same hardware.\n\nServerless functions : AWS Lambda - small, stateless, event-driven\nfunctions. They run in response to triggers like- https request.\nManaged by cloud provider, autoscaled on demand.\nCold start problem. But, AWS team has some strategies to warmup\nby keeping some ready server for each runtime, which basically is\nthe same as our docker containers.\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
