    {
      "id": "9nPJFOk4MlCxKVNT30Evn",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2067.0549787188033,
      "y": 1565.4203946877963,
      "width": 698.927490234375,
      "height": 240,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b2k",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2041508496,
      "version": 760,
      "versionNonce": 1234616944,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1769332711493,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "How to scale docker containers\nat the end of contests when a ton of\nusers are submitting at the same time?\n\nWe can't drop their requests which will ruin test scores etc\n\n1) Pre-scaling : we can do horizontal scaling but needs guesswork on how many containers\n   needs to be up etc.\n2) Dynamic scaling using AWS Fargate for auto-scaling with ECS containers\n    and set limits on CPU and memory to dynamically scale based on load.\n    Still not enough.\n3)  Buffering using msg queues + dynamic scaling",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "How to scale docker containers\nat the end of contests when a ton of\nusers are submitting at the same time?\n\nWe can't drop their requests which will ruin test scores etc\n\n1) Pre-scaling : we can do horizontal scaling but needs guesswork on how many containers\n   needs to be up etc.\n2) Dynamic scaling using AWS Fargate for auto-scaling with ECS containers\n    and set limits on CPU and memory to dynamically scale based on load.\n    Still not enough.\n3)  Buffering using msg queues + dynamic scaling",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
